The paper presents deterministic parameterized algorithms for packing and matching problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and combinatorics. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are likely sub-categories. The algorithms also involve geometric concepts, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions improving previously known bounds on the problems, indicating a connection to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
